Absolutely! Here’s your complete delivery package for ***Neon District: Open City*** Playtest Roadmap — including:

1. ✅ **Printable Phase Test Checklists (PDF-ready)**  
2. ✅ **Sample Survey Questions for Accessibility & General Feedback**  
3. ✅ **Unity C# Scripts** for camera switching & view transitions  

Let’s break it down.

---

## 📄 **1. Printable Playtest Phase Checklists (PDF-Ready)**  
*(Copy/paste into Word/Google Docs → format as table, or export to PDF)*

### 🔹 **Phase 0: Pre-Playtest Prep Checklist**
| Task | Status (✓) | Notes |
|------|------------|-------|
| Build Unity project with URP + LOD Group enabled | ☐ | Set `Max Level of Detail` to 2 on mobile builds |
| Create 5 platform builds (iOS, Android, PC, macOS, Switch) | ☐ | Use `-batchmode -nographics` for headless iOS build test |
| Integrate Firebase Crashlytics & GameAnalytics | ☐ | Tag events: `view_switch`, `char_created`, `fps_drop` |
| Verify all models use ≤5k tris (mobile) / ≤15k (PC) | ☐ | Use Unity’s Build Report → “Mesh Triangle Count” |
| Design simple 1-block prototype (housing + gas station) | ☐ | Include 1 door, 1 window, 1 interactive kiosk |

---

### 🔹 **Phase 1: Internal Alpha Checklist**
| Test Focus | Pass Criteria |
|------------|---------------|
| Camera Switch (F1 ↔ F3 ↔ Iso) | Avg time < 1.0s; no clipping |
| Character Creation Flow | ≤4 min avg, 0 fatal errors |
| FPS Stability (mobile) | ≥45 fps over 2-min roam loop |
| First-Time UX | ≥80% succeed on first try *without instructions* |

**Bug Triage Key**:  
🔴 Critical = crash or unresponsive camera  
🟡 Major = UI stuck, controls misaligned on mobile  
🟢 Minor = texture pop-in, inconsistent shadow quality

---

### 🔹 **Phase 2–4: Device & Accessibility Checklist**
| Task | Mobile (Touch) | PC (Keyboard/Mouse) | Switch/Controller |
|------|----------------|---------------------|-------------------|
| View switch latency | ≤0.8s | ≤0.5s | ≤1.0s (A/B buttons + stick press) |
| First-person movement stability | No drift after 10 sec | Gyro toggle works | Stick tilt sensitivity ≤20° = 100% pitch |
| UI accessibility (contrast) | ≥6.5:1 (AA+ per WCAG) | Same, plus screen reader (NVDA/JAWS) | VoiceOver + switch control mapping |
| Auto-run + jump | Tap to start/stop | `W` hold = auto-run; space = jump | Right stick click = toggle |

✅ **Accessibility Must-Haves**  
- [ ] “Reduced Motion” toggle in settings  
- [ ] Colorblind mode (deuteranopia/tritanopia presets)  
- [ ] Screen reader navigation on all menus  

---

### 🔹 **Phase 5: Live Playtest Survey Prompt Script**
> 📱 *After each session, show this overlay for ≤10 seconds:*  
> **“Was the view switch helpful?”**  
> 😊 Yes — helped me plan my route  
> 😐 Neutral — didn’t hurt or help much  
> ❌ No — confusing/distracting  

> 💡 *Ask in post-session survey (email/Discord):*  
> **“What part of character creation took the longest? Why?”**  
> [Text box]

---

## 🗣️ **2. Sample Survey Questions**

### 🔸 General Playtest Feedback (Post-Session)
1. How intuitive was switching between camera views? *(1–5 scale)*  
2. Was first-person movement comfortable? (Yes/No + why)  
3. Did you use Isometric view to plan routes? When?  
4. What would make character customization *easier* or *faster*?  
5. [Mobile only] Did your phone get hot during play? (Yes/No, duration)

### 🔸 Accessibility-Focused Survey *(Share separately with testers who identify as having disabilities)*
| Question | Response Format |
|----------|-----------------|
| Can you navigate the main menu using screen reader (VoiceOver/NVDA)? | Yes / Partially / No → If partially: What fails? |
| Are the color sliders (skin/hair) distinguishable for color vision deficiency? *(Show sample)* | ☐ Deuteranopia-friendly ☐ Tritanopia-friendly ☐ None |
| Is “Auto-run” + tap-to-move sufficient for low-mobility players? (Yes/No → suggest alternative) | [ ] Yes [ ] No + suggestion: ________ |
| Does the game include a way to disable camera sway in first-person? (e.g., Reduced Motion toggle) | ☐ Yes, and it works well ☐ Yes, but broken ☐ No |

> 🎯 **Best Practice**: Offer $1 gift card for each completed accessibility survey.

---

## 💻 **3. Unity C# Scripts**

### ✅ Script #1: Camera Switch Manager (Cross-Platform)
```csharp
// CameraManager.cs — attach to empty GameObject in scene
using UnityEngine;

public class CameraManager : MonoBehaviour
{
    public enum ViewMode { Isometric, ThirdPerson, FirstPerson }

    [Header("References")]
    public Transform player;
    public Camera mainCamera;

    [Header("View Settings")]
    public Vector3 isoOffset = new(0f, 12f, -8f);  // Isometric offset (top-down angled)
    public float isoFOV = 40f;
    public float cameraLerpSpeed = 5f;

    private ViewMode currentMode = ViewMode.ThirdPerson;

    void Start()
    {
        SwitchView(ViewMode.ThirdPerson); // Default
        mainCamera.fieldOfView = isoFOV;
    }

    // PUBLIC API — call from UI, input, or keyboard/touch
    public void SwitchView(ViewMode mode)
    {
        currentMode = mode;

        switch (mode)
        {
            case ViewMode.Isometric:
                mainCamera.transform.position = player.position + isoOffset;
                mainCamera.transform.rotation = Quaternion.Euler(45f, 30f, 0f);
                break;

            case ViewMode.ThirdPerson:
                mainCamera.transform.SetParent(player); // child to player
                mainCamera.transform.localPosition = new Vector3(0f, 2.5f, -4f);
                mainCamera.transform.localRotation = Quaternion.identity;
                break;

            case ViewMode.FirstPerson:
                mainCamera.transform.SetParent(player);
                mainCamera.transform.localPosition = new Vector3(0f, 1.6f, 0.8f); // head height
                mainCamera.transform.localRotation = Quaternion.identity;
                break;
        }
    }

    void LateUpdate()
    {
        // Smoothly lerp back if camera got displaced (e.g., during transition)
        switch (currentMode)
        {
            case ViewMode.Isometric:
                Vector3 targetPos = player.position + isoOffset;
                mainCamera.transform.position = 
                    Vector3.Lerp(mainCamera.transform.position, targetPos, Time.deltaTime * cameraLerpSpeed);
                break;

            case ViewMode.ThirdPerson:
            case ViewMode.FirstPerson:
                // Camera follows player (via parent)
                break;
        }
    }

    // INPUT BINDING HELPERS
#if UNITY_INPUT_SYSTEM
    public void OnToggleView() 
    {
        ViewMode next = currentMode switch {
            ViewMode.Isometric => ViewMode.ThirdPerson,
            ViewMode.ThirdPerson => ViewMode.FirstPerson,
            ViewMode.FirstPerson => ViewMode.Isometric
        };
        SwitchView(next);
    }
#endif
}
```

#### Usage:
- Add `Input System` actions:  
  - `Toggle View → Space` (PC) / `Double-tap screen center` (mobile via script)  
- In mobile UI, add a toggle button that calls `cameraManager.SwitchView(ViewMode.Isometric)`  

---

### ✅ Script #2: Camera Transition Smoothness & Stability Fix
```csharp
// SmoothCameraTransition.cs — attach to main camera
using UnityEngine;

[RequireComponent(typeof(Camera))]
public class SmoothCameraTransition : MonoBehaviour
{
    [Header("Settings")]
    public float transitionDuration = 0.5f;
    public bool useGyroForFPSSmooth = true;
    private Quaternion initialRotation;
    private Coroutine transitionRoutine;

    void Start()
    {
        initialRotation = transform.rotation;
    }

    // Call this when switching views
    public void BeginTransition()
    {
        if (transitionRoutine != null)
            StopCoroutine(transitionRoutine);
        transitionRoutine = StartCoroutine(SmoothLerp());
    }

    IEnumerator SmoothLerp()
    {
        float elapsed = 0f;

        Quaternion targetRot = transform.rotation;
        Vector3 startPos = transform.position;

        while (elapsed < transitionDuration)
        {
            float t = elapsed / transitionDuration;

            // Ease-out Quad for natural feel
            float ease = t * (2 - t); 

            transform.position = Vector3.Lerp(startPos, transform.position, ease);
            transform.rotation = Quaternion.Slerp(initialRotation, targetRot, ease);

            // Optional: Reduce FOV judder in FP by dampening pitch/yaw jitter
            if (useGyroForFPSSmooth && Application.isMobilePlatform)
                ApplyGyroStabilization();

            elapsed += Time.unscaledDeltaTime;
            yield return null;
        }

        transform.rotation = targetRot; // Lock final rotation
    }

#if ENABLE_INPUT_SYSTEM && UNITY_ANDROID
    void ApplyGyroStabilization()
    {
        // Simple low-pass filter on Gyro attitude (if using VR or head tracking)
        if (Input.gyro.attitude != Quaternion.identity)
        {
            transform.rotation *= Quaternion.Slerp(
                Input.gyro.attitude, 
                Quaternion.identity, 
                0.2f
            );
        }
    }
#endif
}
```

> 📌 **Tip**: Call `cameraManager.SwitchView(...)` → *immediately followed by* `GetComponent<SmoothCameraTransition>().BeginTransition()`

---

### ✅ Script #3: Mobile View-Switch Trigger (Double-Tap to Isometric)
```csharp
// MobileCameraInput.cs — for touch devices only
using UnityEngine;

public class MobileCameraInput : MonoBehaviour
{
    public CameraManager cameraManager;
    private float tapTime = 0f;
    private const float TAP_WINDOW = 0.3f; // seconds between taps

    void Update()
    {
        if (Input.touchCount > 0 && Input.GetTouch(0).phase == TouchPhase.Began)
        {
            Vector2 touchPos = Input.GetTouch(0).position;

            // Only count center taps (not UI touches)
            if (IsTapInCenterScreen(touchPos))
            {
                float now = Time.unscaledTime;
                if (now - tapTime < TAP_WINDOW)
                {
                    // Double-tap detected → toggle to Isometric
                    cameraManager.SwitchView(CameraManager.ViewMode.Isometric);
                }
                tapTime = now;
            }
        }
    }

    bool IsTapInCenterScreen(Vector2 pos)
    {
        float centerX = Screen.width / 2f;
        float centerY = Screen.height / 2f;
        return Vector2.Distance(pos, new Vector2(centerX, centerY)) < Screen.width * 0.15f; // ±15% screen radius
    }
}
```

> 📱 Place on `Canvas` or global input manager.

---

